<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1893,2026]" lastBlockId="6.[199,1436,151,212]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1966,1990]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[273,503,1966,1990]" class="Malacostraca" family="Stenopodidae" genus="Stenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrsonotus">
<emphasis box="[273,503,1966,1990]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Stenopus pyrsonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a shallow-water species common in caves the Marquesas between 
<quantity box="[1275,1376,1965,1989]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">
20– 
<specimenCount box="[1318,1376,1965,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" type="generic">35 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. This species was photographed by the ROV at 
<quantity box="[702,780,2001,2025]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.29" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="129.0">129 m</quantity>
, being its deepest record. A specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1436,2002,2025]" class="Malacostraca" family="Stenopodidae" genus="Stenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrsonotus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1436,2002,2025]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. pyrsonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in 
<number box="[337,393,151,175]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" value="1997.0">1997</number>
with a dredge at 
<quantity box="[589,689,151,175]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" metricValueMax="8.7" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" unit="m" value="86.0" valueMax="87.0" valueMin="85.0">85–87 m</quantity>
off Hiva Oa (R/V 
<emphasis box="[901,944,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Alis</emphasis>
, unpublished record, MUSORSTOM 
<number box="[1374,1390,151,175]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" value="9.0">9</number>
, stn DW 
<number box="[248,303,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" value="1217.0">1217</number>
) confirms the observations made with the ROV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
